# This file describes installing Jenkins and Git on same Ubuntu 14.04 server.

1. Download Jenkins repository key to a file say "jenkins.key"
   $ wget -q -O - http://pkg.jenkins-ci.org/debian/jenkins-ci.org.key
   
2. Add the key
   $ sudo apt-key add jenkins.key
   OK

3. Add the Jenkins repo to sources file in apt
   $ sudo sh -c 'echo deb http://pkg.jenkins-ci.org/debian binary/ > /etc/apt/sources.list.d/jenkins.list'
   
4. Update 
   $ sudo apt-get update

5. Install Jenkins
   $ sudo apt-get install jenkins
   
   Jenkins will automatically start.

   Access its UI from URL:
      http://jenkins_server_ip:8080

6. Install Git
    $ sudo apt-get install git
    
7. Install Git plugin in Jenkins through UI.
    On the left pane of Jenkins nome page, go to "Manage Jenkins" --> "Manage plugins" --> "Available" tab and select "Git plugin" and "GitHub plugin".

8. Click on "Install without restart". 

9. Restart the Jenkins server whenever necessary
    $ sudo servioce jenkins restart
    
10.Configure Git plugin with your Git username and mail id.
    On the left pane of Jenkins nome page, go to "Manage Jenkins" --> "Configure System". 
    Under "Git" heading, add "Git name" and Git executable located in the system.
    Under "Git plugin" heading, add your GitHub username and mail id.
    
